"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The use of `reset_index(drop=True)` after `apply` is incorrect because it attempts to reset the index of the entire DataFrame returned by `apply`, which is not a Series. This will lead to a ValueError since the lengths of the resulting Series and the original DataFrame do not match.\",\n  \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(drop=True)\\n---\\n> df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).transform('sum')\"\n}"